Aguero Will Cost Manchester City $147 Million, Sun Says: Soccer Roundup

-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 
2011-07-28T09:33:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/aguero-will-cost-manchester-city-147-million-sun-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  City Record  Sergio Aguero  will cost Manchester City 90 million pounds
($147.1 million) in fee and salary, making him its most-
expensive signing,  the Sun  reported.  City agreed to a 38 million-pound transfer fee with
 Atletico Madrid  for the striker and agreed to pay him 200,000
pounds-a-week over five years, the Sun said.  Robinho was City’s previous most costly signing when he
signed in a 32.5 million-pound transfer from Real  Madrid  in 2008.  Cesc Replacement  Arsenal is close to signing Juan Mata for 15 million pounds,
which may allow Cesc Fabregas to join Barcelona, the  Daily
Mirror  reported.  The Valencia midfielder’s family and representatives
arrived in  London  yesterday for talks, the Mirror said.  Chelsea Bid  Chelsea bid 20 million euros ($29 million) for 18-year-old
Anderlecht striker Romelu Lukaku, the  Daily Mail  reported.  A previous offer of 18 million euros was rejected, the Mail
said. The Blues are also interested in signing 22-year-old
Palermo midfielder Javier Pastore, who may join Paris-Saint
Germain for 39 million pounds, the Mail added.  Birmingham Exodus  Ben Foster , Liam Ridgewell and Nikola Zigic are among
Birmingham players seeking to leave because of the team’s
financial woes,  the Sun  reported.  If Birmingham can’t pay off its debts it could be put into
administration, according to the Sun.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Alex Duff in Madrid  at
 aduff4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
